    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's not just a \"dry spell.\" it feels permanent. like the version of me that actually mattered is just... gone. i keep thinking that if the thing that defined me is dead, then there's really no point in just sitting around waiting for a ghost to come back. it feels like i'm just taking up space.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the thing that defined you is gone, then maybe it's time to stop trying to resurrect a dead version of yourself. You are not just \"taking up space\"; you are a collection of experiences that are currently unorganized, and that's okay. Instead of waiting for a ghost, consider what you'd do if you decided to make a new, smaller, less ambitious thing—something just for the act of doing, not for the outcome.",
      "source": "target",
